The paper introduces a new class of end-to-end learnable models that can be implemented in popular deep learning software libraries. The paper focuses on the application of these models for image and point cloud classification tasks, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the back-propagation of gradients through declaratively defined data processing nodes, which is a key aspect of neural networks and suggests that the paper could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of declarative and imperative nodes within the same network, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the mathematical optimization problems that define the forward function of the network, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
